⊢ inbox
  given messages[] ≡ [
    "Please summarize the Q3 report",
    "What's the status of Project Alpha?",
    "Schedule a meeting with engineering"
  ]
  yield §handlers[]

  ∴ For each message in «messages», create a handler cell
    that processes that message. Each handler should:
    - Classify the message type (query, request, task)
    - Generate an appropriate response
    - Yield: type, response, needs-action (boolean)

  ⊨ §handlers has same length as «messages»
  ⊨ each handler has given message, yield type/response/needs-action

⊢ dispatch
  given inbox→§handlers
  yield results[]

  ∴ Execute each handler cell from «inbox→§handlers».
    Collect their outputs into results.

  ⊨ results has same length as «inbox→§handlers»

⊢ act
  given dispatch→results
  yield actions[]

  ∴ For each result where needs-action is true, create
    an action item. For queries, the response is sufficient.

  ⊨ actions only contains items where needs-action was true
